.TH "update_preds" 9 "update_preds" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
update_preds \- assign a program entry a label target
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" update_preds
.BI "(struct prog_entry *prog "  ","
.BI "int N "  ","
.BI "int invert "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "prog" 12
The program array
.IP "N" 12
The index of the current entry in \fIprog\fP
.IP "invert" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The program entry at \fIN\fP has a target that points to the index of a program
entry that can have its target and when_to_branch fields updated.
Update the current program entry denoted by index \fIN\fP target field to be
that of the updated entry. This will denote the entry to update if
we are processing an "||" after an "&&"
